Per Capita COVID-19 cases worldwide

GIS plot of per capita cases of COVID-19 all over the world

Jun 28, 2020 • Shantam Raj • 3 min read

geospatial,   interactive,   chloropleth,   NYT

Today we will make the Per Capita covid cases worldwide from the article Coronavirus Map: Tracking the Global Outbreak that looks like the following -

import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
import altair as alt

We will use the JHU CSSE Dataset for the cases as well as the population. For the map we will use a geojson file that I made in the last world chloropleth case growth map.

population_uri = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/master/csse_covid_19_data/UID_ISO_FIPS_LookUp_Table.csv'
population_data = pd.read_csv(population_uri)

latest_cases_uri = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/master/csse_covid_19_data/csse_covid_19_daily_reports/06-24-2020.csv'
latest_cases = pd.read_csv(latest_cases_uri)

world_geojson = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/armsp/covidviz/master/assets/world.geojson'
world = gpd.read_file(world_geojson)

Dropping unnecessary columns and making necessary moniker changes to countries just like we did last time -

latest_cases = latest_cases.drop(['FIPS', 'Admin2', 'Province_State', 'Last_Update', 'Lat', 'Long_', 'Combined_Key', 'Incidence_Rate', 'Case-Fatality_Ratio'], axis=1)
latest_cases = latest_cases.groupby('Country_Region').aggregate({'Confirmed': 'sum', 'Recovered': 'sum', 'Deaths': 'sum', 'Active': 'sum', })
latest_cases = latest_cases.reset_index()

latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Taiwan*', 'Country_Region'] = 'Taiwan'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='US', 'Country_Region'] = 'United States'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Czech Republic', 'Country_Region'] = 'Czechia'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='West Bank and Gaza', 'Country_Region'] = 'West Bank (disp)'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Western Sahara', 'Country_Region'] = 'Western Sahara (disp)'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Trinidad and Tobago', 'Country_Region'] = 'Trinidad & Tobago'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Sao Tome and Principe', 'Country_Region'] = 'Sao Tome & Principe'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Saint Vincent and the Grenadines', 'Country_Region'] = 'St Vincent & the Grenadines'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Saint Lucia', 'Country_Region'] = 'St Lucia'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Saint Kitts and Nevis', 'Country_Region'] = 'St Kitts & Nevis'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='North Macedonia', 'Country_Region'] = 'Macedonia'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Bahamas', 'Country_Region'] = 'Bahamas, The'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Bosnia and Herzegovina', 'Country_Region'] = 'Bosnia & Herzegovina'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Central African Republic', 'Country_Region'] = 'Central African Rep'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Eswatini', 'Country_Region'] = 'Swaziland'
#time_s.loc[time_s['Country/Region']=='South Korea', 'Country/Region'] = 'Korea, South'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Congo (Kinshasa)', 'Country_Region'] = 'Congo, Dem Rep of the'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Congo (Brazzaville)', 'Country_Region'] = 'Congo, Rep of the'
latest_cases.loc[latest_cases['Country_Region']=='Antigua and Barbuda', 'Country_Region'] = 'Antigua & Barbuda'

Extracting population data for countries -

population_data = population_data.drop(['UID', 'code3', 'FIPS', 'Admin2', 'Province_State', 'Lat', 'Long_'], axis=1)
population_data = population_data[population_data['Country_Region'] == population_data['Combined_Key']]
population_data = population_data.reset_index(drop=True)
population_data.head()

population_data.loc[population_data['Country_Region']=='Western Sahara', 'Country_Region'] = 'Western Sahara (disp)'

population_data.loc[population_data['Country_Region']=='Bosnia and Herzegovina', 'Country_Region'] = 'Bosnia & Herzegovina'
population_data.loc[population_data['Country_Region']=='Central African Republic', 'Country_Region'] = 'Central African Rep'
population_data.loc[population_data['Country_Region']=='Eswatini', 'Country_Region'] = 'Swaziland'
#time_s.loc[time_s['Country/Region']=='South Korea', 'Country/Region'] = 'Korea, South'
population_data.loc[population_data['Country_Region']=='Congo (Kinshasa)', 'Country_Region'] = 'Congo, Dem Rep of the'
population_data.loc[population_data['Country_Region']=='Congo (Brazzaville)', 'Country_Region'] = 'Congo, Rep of the'
population_data.loc[population_data['Country_Region']=='Antigua and Barbuda', 'Country_Region'] = 'Antigua & Barbuda'

world.columns = ['Country_Region', 'geometry']
world = world.merge(latest_cases, on='Country_Region', how='left')
world = world.merge(population_data, on='Country_Region', how='left')
world['per_capita'] = world['Confirmed']/world['Population']

world['code'] = world['per_capita'].apply(lambda x: 'Less than 1 in 1000' if x <= (1/1000) else 'Less than 1 in 500' if x<= (1/500) else 'Less than 1 in 333' if x<= (1/333) else 'No Cases reported' if pd.isnull(x) else 'Greater than 1 in 333')
world['Share of Population'] = world['Population']/world['Confirmed']
world['Share of Population'] = world['Share of Population'].round()
world['Share of Population'] = world['Share of Population'].apply(lambda x: f"1 in {str(x).split('.')[0]}")

Making the chart -

alt.Chart(world).mark_geoshape(stroke='white').transform_filter(alt.datum.Country_Region != 'Antarctica').encode(
    color=alt.Color('code:N', scale=alt.Scale(domain=['No Cases reported', 'Less than 1 in 1000', 'Less than 1 in 500', 'Less than 1 in 333', 'Greater than 1 in 333'], range=['lightgrey', '#f2df91', '#ffae43', '#ff6e0b', '#ce0a05']),legend=alt.Legend(title=None, orient='top', labelBaseline='middle', symbolType='square', columnPadding=20, labelFontSize=15, gridAlign='each', symbolSize=200)),
    tooltip = ['Country_Region', 'Confirmed', 'Share of Population']
).properties(width=1400, height=800).project('equalEarth').configure_view(strokeWidth=0)
